yingyinNormal.en: I do not understand why any form of compromise is beyond him. You wanted a strong editor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不明白他怎么就不能接受任何妥协。是你想要个强势的编辑。

yingyinNormal.en: Dana Treister, do you know her? The editor of Vanity Fair. That's right. She's a close friend.
yingyinNormal.zh: 戴娜·崔斯特，你认识吧？《名利场》的编辑。是的，她是我的密友。

yingyinNormal.en: I found my editor. And had some fun, too, I hope. I went dancing at the Cafe de Paris, which felt very young and gay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我找到编辑了。也去找乐子了吧。我去巴黎咖啡厅跳了舞，感觉特别年轻快活。

yingyinNormal.en: I was editor in chief of the Daily Northwestern.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我曾是西北日报的主编。

yingyinNormal.en: Secretary Durant. Editor in chief, Politico. It's all right. Adam, are you covering this yourself?
yingyinNormal.zh: 杜兰特国务卿，我是政治新闻网的总编。没事的，亚当，你亲自来做报道吗？
